planet.description: The Kepler-20 system hosts at least 5 exo-planet. The Kepler team has announced the confirmation of the two smallest planets in the system, Kepler-20 e and Kepler-20 f. Kepler-20 f is orbiting the star every 20 days. It is too close to the star to be habitable. It could have developed a thick water vapour atmosphere.
